payload.message:
Fixed. Root cause was the Supabase Auth trigger: some existing `app.profile` rows had an email but no `auth_user_id`, so first Microsoft SSO tried to insert a duplicate profile email and Supabase returned “Database error saving new user.”

What changed:
- Added a shared-db migration that links pre-seeded profiles by email during first SSO login: [migration](/worksp/shared-db/supabase/migrations/20260703172500_fix_crm_auth_profile_email_link.sql:1)
- Added visible OAuth callback error handling on the login page instead of silently leaving the error in the URL: [LoginPage.tsx](/worksp/popcrm-web/src/pages/LoginPage.tsx:14)

Status:
- Database migration applied to preview and production.
- Production rollback test confirmed the trigger now links the profile successfully.
- App build/deploy completed; `https://crm.designflow.app` is serving the new commit.
- The affected users should try “Sign in with Microsoft” again. The 4 pre-seeded profiles will link as those users retry.

Verification passed:
- `npm run build`
- `scripts/check-sql.sh`
- shared-db PR checks
- production deployment workflow

