Found it. `adweck@popcre.com` was a different case than the first fix covered.

His CRM `app.profile.email` is `adweck@popcre.com`, but that profile was already linked to an older Auth user whose email is `adamsdweck@gmail.com` and provider is Google. My first migration only relinked profiles where `auth_user_id` was null, so Adam’s profile still caused the duplicate-email failure during Microsoft SSO.

Fixed now:
- Added shared-db migration `20260703220000_fix_crm_auth_profile_mismatched_email_relink.sql`
- Applied to preview and production
- Verified with a rollbacked production test for `adweck@popcre.com`: the trigger successfully relinked the profile to the newly inserted Microsoft auth user
- Merged through shared-db PR #39 into `main`

Adam should try Microsoft sign-in again now. On successful retry, his profile will relink from the old Gmail Auth user to the new Microsoft Auth user.

Also, the frontend global error banner is live at commit `e2d8d45`, so if anything still fails, the error should be visible instead of silently sitting in the URL.

